title: About
text:
The [Bio/Diversity Project] (https://biodiversityproject.arizona.edu/) is a collaborative effort between [WISE] (https://wise.arizona.edu/) , [Saguaro National Park] (https://www.nps.gov/sagu/index.htm) and the [Friends of Saguaro National Park] (https://www.friendsofsaguaro.org/), with additional support from local environmental organizations, aimed at increasing the diversity of voices included in discussions of environmental problems and the development of their solutions. By increasing access to innovative environmental science educational opportunities and training, mentoring, and work experience along the K-16+ educational pipeline, we aim to get students excited about environmental science and support them along their educational journeys and into the workforce.
